news.title: Bengaluru civic body to conduct another survey of buildings' condition
news.para: BBMP Chief Commissioner Gaurav Gupta said," I have asked them to take up another survey on the condition of buildings in the city. A team led by joint commissioners will take up the survey at the zonal levels. Currently, the focus will be on the south zone where I have asked the officials to complete a fresh survey within 30 days.”

news.title: Nagpur civic body protected illegal terrace flat for 20 months by lying that matter is in court
news.para: West Nagpur MLA Vikas Thakre wrote to municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B on September 27, asking for the reasons behind inaction against the unauthorized flat. He also asked the civic chief to give detailed information about pending action against unauthorized constructions in the city.

news.title: Goa government to compensate 322 damaged houses in Bicholim
news.para: Bicholim mamlatdar Pravinjay Pandit said that six houses will be reconstructed completely by the state government in collaboration with the Rotary Club International, beginning next week.
